width /wɪdθ, ˈwɪtθ/

(widths) 

1. N-VAR The width of something is the distance it measures from one side or edge to the other. 宽度 

例： Measure the full width of the window. 测量一下窗户的总宽度。 

例： The road was reduced to 18 ft in width by adding parking bays. 这条路增加了停车区域后，宽度减少为18英尺。

